com.idevicesinc.sweetblue.utils

Class BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.BluetoothEnablerEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.idevicesinc.sweetblue.utils.Event
      • com.idevicesinc.sweetblue.utils.BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.BluetoothEnablerEvent
  • Enclosing interface:
    BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter

    public static class BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.BluetoothEnablerEvent
extends Event
    Events passed to BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.onEvent(BluetoothEnablerEvent) so that the programmer can assign logic to the user's decision to enable or disable certain required permissions and settings. Each event contains a BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Stage which holds the current enabling stage and a BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Status of that stage. Stages which haven't been performed yet start off as BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Status.NULL, stages skipped are BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Status.SKIPPED and stages that don't need anything done are BluetoothEnabler.BluetoothEnablerFilter.Status.ALREADY_ENABLED. Otherwise, the status of the stage is whatever the user selected.
